(80, 2, 0, 'Davidoff Hutcher & Citron LLP Expands Federal Government Relations Group With the Additions of Russ Klenet and Jonathan McCollum in DC Office', '', '2013-01-25 00:00:00', '2013-01-27 18:41:15', '<p>Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP adds another dimension to its government relations practice by expanding its existing Federal Government Relations Group.&nbsp; The Federal Government Relations group will be led by lobbyist Russ Klenet, who will serve as Chair. Jonathan McCollum will assist Klenet as Director of Government Relations.&nbsp; Based in Washington D.C., Klenet and McCollum will lend their expertise to ongoing and new public policy lobbying initiatives taking place nationally and throughout the New York metropolitan area. </p>\r\n<p>Russ Klenet &lsquo;s broad based knowledge enhances Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron&rsquo;s already robust Government Relations Group, having founded his own lobbying firm, Russ Klenet &amp; Associates, in 1998.&nbsp; Russ Klenet&rsquo;s experience is unusually broad, having represented an array of interests including Fortune 500 health care, telecom and energy firms and created a special practice representing local governments to state and federal agencies.&nbsp; Additionally, Russ Klenet has represented Financial Services firms on Wall Street and was involved in the passage of Dodd-Frank and the Consumer Protection Act.&nbsp; He has negotiated complicated energy deals for clients, blending public and private components in order to secure project financing and development.&nbsp; Russ Klenet has particularized experience in the field of International trade financing and navigating the awarding and maintaining of GSA Schedule Contracts, which is vital to the lifeblood of vendors who wish to service the needs of governments at all levels nationwide in a quick manner that circumvents the arduous RFP process.&nbsp; As someone who played a leading role in Florida on behalf of the current presidential administration, Klenet solidifies his connection to the Hill and within the corridors of Washington.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Through his relationships on the Hill and within the current administration, McCollum successfully leads the clients of Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron through complicated legislative and administrative issues.&nbsp; McCollum&rsquo;s previous experience includes campaign work, having managed state-wide, mayoral, and over thirty municipal campaigns.&nbsp; He also worked alongside Klenet by managing the Washington D.C. operation of Russ Klenet &amp; Associates.&nbsp; By working with Klenet, McCollum has represented a diverse group of clients, gaining significant experience in federal procurements, international trade, alternative energy and education policy.</p>\r\n<p>Currently, the Federal Government Relations Group is managing projects and procurements for clients at the Department of Education, Health &amp; Human Services, Commerce and the Treasury among others.&nbsp; Of particular note is the firm&rsquo;s ongoing role in lobbying on behalf of businesses and other entities that were impacted by the devastation caused by Hurricane Sandy.</p>', 'russ klenet,Jonathan McCollum,governement relations lawyer new york', 0x44617669646f66662048757463686572202620436974726f6e204c4c5020457870616e6473204665646572616c20476f7665726e6d656e742052656c6174696f6e732047726f7570205769746820746865204164646974696f6e73206f662052757373204b6c656e657420616e64204a6f6e617468616e204d63436f6c6c756d20696e204443204f6666696365, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Davidoff-Hutcher-and-Citron-LLP-Expands-Federal-Government-Relations-Group-With-the-Additions-of-Russ-Klenet-and-Jonathan-McCollum-in-DC-Office', 0, ''),
