(84, 2, 0, 'Sid Davidoff Speaks about Ed Koch', '', '2013-02-01 00:00:00', '2013-02-04 07:21:38', '<p>Sid Davidoff is a special guest on&nbsp;Good Day New York to speak about the passing of former New York City Mayor Ed Koch.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://ctv4.criticalmention.com/playerpage/player?params=Y2xpcElkPTUyMjgzNTYmc2xpbT0xJnBvd2VyZWQ9MSZyZXBvcnQ9dHJ1ZSZoaWRlQ2xpcENvbnRyb2xzPTEmbm9oZWFkZXI9MSZub21lbnU9dHJ1ZSZhdXRvUGxheT0xJnBhcnRuZXJUb2tlbj04YTMzNjVmYzNjMmE5NzIzMDEzYzk3MzcwZDA5MjM5OA==">See the video</a><br /><br /></p>', 'Ed Koch dies, Ed Koch New York City', 0x5369642044617669646f66662069732061207370656369616c206775657374206f6e20476f6f6420446179204e657720596f726b20746f20737065616b2061626f7574207468652070617373696e67206f6620666f726d6572204e657720596f726b2043697479204d61796f72204564204b6f63682e, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Sid-Davidoff-Speaks-about-Ed-Koch', 0, ''),
(85, 4, 0, 'Russ Klenet arranges a tour for Matthew S. Erskine to gain a first-hand look at the devastation  of Superstorm Sandy.', '', '2013-02-06 21:28:27', '2013-02-06 21:37:32', '<p><a href="../../../attorneys/Russ-Klenet">Russ Klenet</a>, Chair of the Federal Government Relations Group at&nbsp;<a href="../../../">Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP</a>, along with the firm&rsquo;s DC office, arranged a tour for&nbsp;<a href="http://www.eda.gov/about/bios/bio_erskine.htm">Matthew S. Erskine</a>, Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for the U.S. Economic Development Administration, of the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.madelainechocolate.com/">The Madelaine Chocolate Company</a>&nbsp;in Rockaway, New York on January 30, 2013 to gain a first-hand look at the devastation of Superstorm Sandy.&nbsp;&nbsp;The tour was followed by a Reception in Howard Beach, another area still recovering from Sandy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The tour invitation extended to Erskine demonstrated the desire of local politicians to open the dialogue about the relief efforts being undertaken by the Federal Government to respond to the devastation wrought by Sandy.&nbsp; Spearheaded by Jorge Farber, Norman Gold and Vivian Farber, Senior Management of Madelaine, the tour was led by DHC Managing Partner Jeff Citron and DHC Washington Director, Jonathan McCollum. &nbsp;Congressman Gregory Meeks, who represents New York&rsquo;s 5<sup>th</sup> District, along with <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">and</span> several <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">other</span> state and local leaders were <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">also</span> on hand to help lead the tour. &nbsp; Secretary Erskine met with many of the employees and committed the Office of Economic Development to use its resources to help Madelaine recover from the storm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Established in 1949 and&nbsp;located in Far Rockaway, Queens, The Madelaine Chocolate Company is an American family-owned and run company whose chocolates are made solely in New York.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Madelaine is one of the Rockaways'' largest employers with 450 employees, all of whom are now out of a job.</p>\r\n<p>At the Reception, sponsored by the Queens Chamber of Commerce, Secretary Erskine, Congressman Meeks, Congressman&nbsp;<a href="http://hakeemjeffries.com/">Hakeem Jeffries</a>, who&nbsp;represents&nbsp;<a title="New York''s 8th congressional district" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York%27s_8th_congressional_district">New York''s 8th Congressional District</a>, and local leaders all re-affirmed their commitments to bringing a coordinated recovery response to residences and businesses struggling to recover.</p>\r\n<p>Please let me know if you are interested in speaking with&nbsp;<a href="../../../attorneys/Russ-Klenet">Russ Klenet</a>, to learn more about the event and relief efforts that were discussed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Russ Klenet, super storm sandy, hurricane sandy, government relations lawyer', , 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Russ-Klenet-arranges-a-tour-for-Matthew-S--Erskine-to-gain-a-first-hand-look-at-the-devastation--of-Superstorm-Sandy-', 0, ''),
