(91, 2, 0, 'Denenberg''s district restored to proposed new map', '', '2013-02-27 00:00:00', '2013-02-28 07:33:59', '<p><span class="userContent">Nassau Republicans have agreed to restore DHC Partner and Legis. David Denenberg (D-Merrick) to his longtime district after Legis. Denise Ford bucked GOP leaders and refused to vote for new legislative lines at a marathon meeting Monday.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span class="userContent"><a href="http://bit.ly/WfqTkV" rel="nofollow nofollow" target="_blank">http://bit.ly/WfqTkV</a></span></p>', 'Redistrict, Denenberg', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Denenberg-s-district-restored-to-proposed-new-map', 0, ''),
(95, 2, 0, 'BLOOMBERG  ''Enemy'' Davidoff: Business of Law', '', '2013-03-12 00:00:00', '2013-03-13 05:35:50', '<p>By Elizabeth Amon - Mar 12, 2013 12:01 AM ET</p>\r\n<p><br />After Sid Davidoff was anointed public enemy number 12 by President Richard Nixon almost 40 years ago, the political operative for former New York City Mayor John F. Lindsay turned to the law.<br /><br />&ldquo;It was a defining moment,&rdquo; the Davidoff, Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP partner said in a telephone interview yesterday. &ldquo;I realized that with my law degree and knowledge of government, this was the time for me to get into the practice of law to do what I do best -- take on the government in some fashion on behalf of clients who can&rsquo;t get the government to understand what they want to do and why they want to do it.&rdquo;<br /><br />At an event today sponsored by Common Cause in Washington commemorating the 40-year anniversary of Watergate, Davidoff will be among three people attending who were on Nixon&rsquo;s top 20 enemies list, said Common Cause&rsquo;s Gary Ferdman. About 20 others who were on an expanded enemies list will either attend in person or will be represented.<br /><br />Among those on the top 20 list were labor union organizers, journalists, Nixon&rsquo;s political opponents and Hollywood celebrities, including former government adviser Morton Halperin and U.S. Representative John Conyers, who will both attend the ceremony.<br /><br />Davidoff said testimony at the time revealed that Nixon believed that Lindsay, a former ally, had the potential to hurt Nixon&rsquo;s career but was thought to be too difficult a target, making Davidoff the next best thing.<br /><br />&ldquo;I was his political lieutenant. I was in charge of his troops,&rdquo; Davidoff recalled about Lindsay. &ldquo;Take down the leadership in the field, I guess that&rsquo;s what they thought.&rdquo;<br /><br />Davidoff said he realized after the list was made public in 1974 that he had been the target of government harassment through Internal Revenue Service audits and by snooping strangers.<br /><br />Ferdman said Davidoff&rsquo;s experience showed the outrageousness of the political climate. &ldquo;He was acting as a patriotic American engaged in the political process,&rdquo; Ferdman said.<br /><br />Within a year of the announcement, Davidoff, who had left the Lindsay administration, joined a small law firm. The name has changed several times, but Davidoff, Hutcher &amp; Citron has grown to more than 50 lawyers in four offices in New York, Albany, Washington and Long Island.<br /><br />While the firm once focused primarily on government relations, it now has a broad commercial practice that includes intellectual property, trusts and estates and other matters.<br /><br />Despite the passage of time, Davidoff said he continues to be asked about the experience, which had a benefit Nixon probably couldn&rsquo;t have imagined. New clients often want to meet him because of his inclusion and the notoriety helped generate business for his practice. &ldquo;It is definitely a badge of distinction,&rdquo; he said.<br /><br />http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-12/-enemy-davidoff-nixon-peabody-bird-business-of-law.html</p>', 'government relations lawyers new york', 0x424c4f4f4d424552472020e28098456e656d79e280992044617669646f66663a20427573696e657373206f66204c6177, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'BLOOMBERG---Enemy--Davidoff--Business-of-Law', 0, 'BLOOMBERG  â€˜Enemyâ€™ Davidoff: Business of Law'),
(96, 2, 0, 'Nixon''s ''Enemies'' Gather This Week in Washington', '', '2013-03-13 00:00:00', '2013-03-13 10:52:48', '<p>Sid Davidoff was standing at the reception area of the midtown Manhattan restaurant he owned when he saw his face splashed across the television.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Hey Sid, you&rsquo;re on TV!&rdquo; restaurant patrons yelled as the phone lines began ringing off the hook with journalists calling to score an interview with Davidoff, who was the chief administrative assistant to New York Mayor John V. Lindsay at the time.</p>\r\n<p>Although Davidoff was well known as Lindsay&rsquo;s political aide, he wasn&rsquo;t used to being in the spotlight and he was confused as to why his likeness was suddenly splashed across the news and why a host of journalists now had an interest in him.</p>\r\n<p>The details, coming as White House Counsel John Dean provided the Senate Watergate Committee evidence of the president&rsquo;s enemies list, quickly came together.</p>\r\n<p>Dean&rsquo;s June 1973 submission of a host of documents related to the Watergate scandal revealed Davidoff&rsquo;s name &mdash; along with 19 others &mdash; was on President Richard Nixon&rsquo;s &ldquo;Opponents and Political Enemies List.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The enemies list was a group of people Nixon thought were trying to derail his quest for a second term and whom he wanted to &ldquo;screw&rdquo; by using tactics such as tax audits to try to bring them down. Davidoff was No. 12 on the list. The memo described him as &ldquo;a first class S.O.B., wheeler-dealer and suspected bagman. Positive results would really shake the Lindsay camp and Lindsay&rsquo;s plans to capture youth vote. Davidoff in charge.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Now, to celebrate the 40th anniversary of the revelation of the list, Davidoff will join other Nixon enemies, as well as their surviving family members, as part of the &ldquo;Lessons of Watergate&rdquo; conference being held Wednesday and Thursday at the National Press Club.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;For me, the fact that this was exposed was so crazy, and I&rsquo;m looking forward to talk about it with some of the people who had similar experiences,&rdquo; Davidoff said of the upcoming gathering of the surviving members of the list.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Enemy of the People</strong></p>\r\n<p>Being an enemy of the state was never in Davidoff&rsquo;s plans.</p>\r\n<p>A lawyer by trade, he was interested in public service and government affairs and signed on as an aide to Lindsay, an ambitious politician who had served in the House and was on the shortlist as a potential Nixon vice presidential candidate in the 1968 election.</p>\r\n<p>But in 1971, Lindsay ditched the Republican Party and launched a bid for president in the Democratic primary.</p>\r\n<p>Although he never got the chance to ask anyone with knowledge of the situation, Davidoff is almost certain this ticked Nixon off and was the reason Davidoff got caught in the web.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;You had a mayor who at the time was very visible; he was a superstar in a lot of ways, doing the &lsquo;Tonight Show.&rsquo; He really understood media, and it was difficult to bring him down,&rdquo; Davidoff said of his boss. &ldquo;I was probably the easier target, and sometimes when you bring down the person standing next to you, you get caught in that web, and I think that&rsquo;s what they hoped for.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>When he first realized he was on Nixon&rsquo;s enemies list, Davidoff said he poked fun at the situation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.rollcall.com/news/nixons_enemies_gather_this_week_in_washington-223054-1.html">http://www.rollcall.com/news/nixons_enemies_gather_this_week_in_washington-223054-1.html</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Davidoff, Nixon', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Nixon-s--Enemies--Gather-This-Week-in-Washington', 0, ''),
(97, 4, 0, 'Sid Davidoff, Member of an Esteemed list of Nixonâ€™s Enemies', '', '2013-03-14 20:49:28', '2013-03-15 10:15:58', '<p>Sid Davidoff, Member of an Esteemed list of Nixon&rsquo;s Enemies</p>\r\n<p><object width="300" height="18" data="../../../files/Sid_Davidoff.mp3" type="video/quicktime"><param name="pluginspage" value="http://www.apple.com/quicktime/download/" /><param name="src" value="../../../files/Sid_Davidoff.mp3" /><param name="controller" value="true" /><param name="autoplay" value="autoplay" /><param name="embed" value="" /></object></p>', 'Sid Davidoff, richard nixon, watergate', 0x5369642044617669646f66662c204d656d626572206f6620616e2045737465656d6564206c697374206f66204e69786f6ee280997320456e656d696573, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Sid-Davidoff,-Member-of-an-Esteemed-list-of-Nixonâ€™s-Enemies', 0, 'Government Relations Lawyer, Sid Davidoff, Member of an Esteemed list of Nixonâ€™s Enemies'),
