(106, 2, 0, 'Speaker of the Parliament of the Republic of Mali visits Capitol Hill', '', '2013-05-23 00:00:00', '2013-05-23 12:29:39', '<p>This week, the Washington DC Office of Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron coordinated the visit of the Speaker of the Parliament of the Republic of Mali, Younoussi Tour&eacute;, to visit Capitol Hill. The Speaker was accompanied by Ambassador Al-Mamoun Keita and a Delegation of Members of the Malian Parliament.&nbsp; The Delegation met with Senator Isakson of Georgia and Coons of Delaware in the Senate.&nbsp; In the House the Delegation met with the Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee, Representative Chris Smith of New Jersey.&nbsp; In addition the Delegation met with Representatives Ileana Ros-Lehtinen, Karen Bass, Terri Sewell and others.<br /><br />Here are photos with Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee, Representative Chris Smith of New Jersey and the Speaker of the Parliament of the Republic of Mali, Younoussi Tour&eacute;, and DHC Federal Government Chair, Russ Klenet, Mali Ambassador to the United States Al-Mamoun Keita, Speaker of the Malian Parliament Younoussi Tour&eacute; and House Foreign Affairs Committee Ranking Member Ted Deutch. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From left to right: Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Sub-Committee, Representative Chris Smith of New Jersey and the Speaker of the Parliament of the Republic of Mali, Younoussi Tour&eacute;.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../app/webroot/img/gallery/Image/Chris%20Smith%20Speaker%20Toure.JPG" alt="" width="640" height="480" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From left the right: DHC Federal Government Relations Chair, Russ Klenet, Mali Ambassador to the United States, Al-Mamoun Keita, Speaker of the Malian Parliament, Younoussi Tour&eacute;, and House Foreign Affairs Committee Ranking Member Ted Deutch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../../../app/webroot/img/gallery/Image/Klent%20Keita%20Toure%20Deutch%20r.jpg" alt="" width="638" height="480" /></p>', 'Russ Klenet', 0x476f7665726e6d656e742052656c6174696f6e73204c61777965722052757373204b6c656e6574202d20537065616b6572206f6620746865205061726c69616d656e74206f66207468652052657075626c6963206f66204d616c69207669736974732043617069746f6c2048696c6c, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Speaker-of-the-Parliament-of-the-Republic-of-Mali-visits-Capitol-Hill', 0, 'Speaker of the Parliament of the Republic of Mali visits Capitol Hill'),
(107, 2, 0, 'Peter Crouse Reflects on 25 Years at Davidoff Hutcher & Citron LLP', '', '2013-05-24 00:00:00', '2013-05-24 08:44:36', '<p>As Albany Director of Government Relations, Peter has used his state legislative network and experience to assist in positioning Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron as a top government affairs and lobbying firm.&nbsp; Working in Albany with a staff of 6 when the legislature is in session and a staff of 4 when the legislature is not in session, Peter lobbies on behalf of a wide variety of clients including environmental, education, health care, engineering, taxation, energy, pharmaceutical, and park and natural resources concerns. <br />&nbsp;<br />Peter&rsquo;s current availability of resources is a far cry from when he helped establish the Albany Government Relations practice 25 years ago.&nbsp; Upon graduating from the Maxwell School at Syracuse University with a Masters in Public Administration, and serving for 10 years as a staff member in the New York State Senate in various capacities, he was recruited by the firm.&nbsp; He has since represented over 300 different clients across a wide spectrum of interests.&nbsp; Among noteworthy lobbying efforts was the elimination of the onerous 2 cent container tax on beverages covered under the Returnable Container Act, environmental efforts regulating hazardous, medical and solid waste, the establishment of a Marine Spill Response effort in New York, the creation of the Olympic Regional Development Authority in Lake Placid, and parkland alienation activities required for the new USTA facility in Queens.<br />&nbsp;<br />Peter looks forward to continuing to represent Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron clients in Albany and expand the Government Relations practice.<br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', 'Government Relations lawyer in New York', 0x50657465722043726f757365205265666c65637473206f6e2032352059656172732061742044617669646f66662048757463686572202620436974726f6e204c4c50, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Peter-Crouse-Reflects-on-25-Years-at-Davidoff-Hutcher-and-Citron-LLP', 0, 'Peter Crouse Reflects on 25 Years at Davidoff Hutcher & Citron LLP'),
(109, 2, 0, 'Speaker of the Parliament TourÃ©, the Delegation from Mali and United States Senator Johnny Isaakson of Georgia', '', '2013-05-24 00:00:00', '2013-05-24 11:25:44', '<p><img src="../../../app/webroot/img/gallery/Image/Speaker%20of%20the%20Parliament%20Toure%20-%20the%20Delegation%20from%20Mali%20and%20United%20States%20Senator%20Johnny%20Isaakson%20of%20Georgia__-.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="315" /></p>', 'Speaker of the Parliament TourÃ©, the Delegation from Mali and United States Senator Johnny Isaakson of Georgia', 0x537065616b6572206f6620746865205061726c69616d656e7420546f7572c3a92c207468652044656c65676174696f6e2066726f6d204d616c6920616e6420556e69746564205374617465732053656e61746f72204a6f686e6e7920497361616b736f6e206f662047656f72676961, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Speaker-of-the-Parliament-TourÃ©,-the-Delegation-from-Mali-and-United-States-Senator-Johnny-Isaakson-of-Georgia', 0, 'Speaker of the Parliament TourÃ©, the Delegation from Mali and United States Senator Johnny Isaakson of Georgia'),
(111, 2, 0, 'JEFFREY I. CITRON, OF DAVIDOFF HUTCHER & CITRON LLP, NAMED TOP ATTORNEY IN THE NEW YORK AREA', '', '2013-06-20 00:00:00', '2013-09-10 19:29:59', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NEW YORK, NY (June 20, 2013) &ndash; Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP, a leading law and government relations firm, is pleased to announce that Jeffrey I. Citron, Co-Managing Partner, was named &ldquo;Best Attorney&rdquo; by The New York Enterprise Report (NYER). &nbsp;The 2013 NYER Accountant &amp; Attorney Awards: The Advisors You Need, presented along with Citibank, recognized the top seven accountants and top seven attorneys in the New York tri-state area.</p>\r\n<p>Recipients were selected from more than 80 nominations based on their outstanding commitment to the success of their small and midsize business clients. &ldquo;We understand the impact a great business advisor can have on a business,&rdquo; said Robert Levin, CEO and Publisher of The New York Enterprise Report. &nbsp;"Jeff was chosen based on his outstanding track record of going above and beyond the call of duty."</p>\r\n<p>For over 25 years Mr. &nbsp;Citron has assisted New York privately held companies with all of their legal and businesses needs.&nbsp; Acting as their general counsel, he advises on banking relations, general administration, employment, contract law, real estate leasing and acquisitions, and other business related issues.&nbsp; More specifically, he is successful in helping clients secure financing, grants and other benefits for capital projects through government agency programs, as well as, traditional lending institutions.&nbsp; He has helped countless business owners fulfill their dreams and enrich the communities they operate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Citron received a B.S./B.A. in Real Estate from the American University in Washington, D.C. and is a graduate of Brooklyn Law School. Mr. Citron has served on the boards of numerous Private, Charitable and other Not-for-Profit corporations, including: Young Men&rsquo;s Philanthropic League, United Hebrew Geriatric Center and Fenway Golf Club where he served as President. Most recently, Mr. Citron was named to the Provident Bank NYC Metro Business Leadership Counsel.&nbsp; Mr. Citron is admitted in the United States District Courts for the Southern and Eastern Districts of New York and was an elected delegate to the State Judicial Conference.&nbsp; Mr. Citron resides with his family in Bedford, NY.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I am humbled and thankful for this distinguished recognition by the New York Enterprise Report,&rdquo; said Mr. &nbsp;Citron.&nbsp; &ldquo;I look forward to continuing to help lead my firm and service all the wonderful clients that come to us to assist them with their legal and government affairs needs.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The top accountants and attorneys were revealed during an awards reception on Wednesday, June 19th at the Citibank Executive Conference Center located in New York City.&nbsp;The advisors will be highlighted in a special editorial section within the July/August 2013 issue of NYER, as well as on&nbsp;<a href="http://nyreport.com/">nyreport.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The New York Enterprise Report (<a href="http://www.nyreport.com/">www.nyreport.com</a>) believes that people should have access to the expertise to help them grow their businesses. &nbsp;They have built a peer-to-peer community of entrepreneurs and executives who constantly seek better ways to operate and grow. Through their multi-media platforms, they provide this community with access to knowledge&nbsp; experts and successful entrepreneurs.</p>\r\n<p>Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP <a href="../../../">www.dhclegal.com</a>, which has over 50 attorneys in offices in New York City, Albany, Washington D.C., and Garden City, Long Island, provides legal and government relations services for a varied clientele that include Fortune 500 companies, financial institutions, prominent real estate organizations, developers, leading health and educational institutions, associations and services organizations, as well as other industries throughout the greater metropolitan area.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="center">###</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'New York Lawyer', 0x4a45464652455920492e20434954524f4e2c204e414d454420544f50204154544f524e455920494e20544845204e455720594f524b204152454120, 0, 1, 2, 1, 'JEFFREY-I--CITRON,-OF-DAVIDOFF-HUTCHER-and-CITRON-LLP,-NAMED-TOP-ATTORNEY-IN-THE-NEW-YORK-AREA', 0, ''),
(110, 2, 0, 'EVENT:  Champions of Change', '', '2013-06-11 00:00:00', '2013-06-19 08:08:16', '<p>On Tuesday, June 11th, Jonathan McCollum, DHC Director of Federal Government Affairs, escorted Jennifer Manley, Vice President of Government &amp; Community Affairs for the Queens Library, to the White House for the Champions of Change Awards Ceremony, honoring outstanding libraries and museums around the country.<br /> <br /> The Champions of Change program was created as an opportunity for the White House to feature groups of Americans &ndash; individuals, businesses and organizations &ndash; who are doing extraordinary things to empower and inspire members of their communities.<br /> <br /> Jennifer Manley was one of only twelve award recipients honored Tuesday evening. &nbsp;Jennifer received this prestigious award for being &nbsp;part of the leadership team of Queens Library, one of the busiest libraries in the nation, welcoming over 13 million visitors a year to its 62 library locations. &nbsp;Immigrants make up more than 50 percent of the Borough&rsquo;s population and the library has become a leader in providing services to new immigrants. &nbsp;Thousands of immigrant adults and their families come to the library to learn English, learn about citizenship and become full participants in democratic society.<br /> <br /> DHC represents Queens Library in Washington, D.C. and in coordination with the Queens Library leadership team, advocates for legislation and policy to improve and expand library programs serving the Queens Community.<br /> </p>', 'Events, Government Affairs', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'EVENT---Champions-of-Change', 0, ''),
(117, 2, 0, 'Nyer Spotlights Jeff Citron of Davidoff Hutcher & Citron', '', '2013-09-13 00:00:00', '2013-09-13 12:11:35', '<p><strong>NYER</strong></p>\r\n<p>The 2013 NYER CPA &amp; Esq. Awards: The Advisors You Need to Know</p>\r\n<p><em>By:</em><em>&nbsp;</em><a href="http://www.nyreport.com/authors/65254/lee_connor"><em>Lee Lusardi Connor</em></a><em></em></p>\r\n<p><em>July /August 2013</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The best entrepreneurs are passionate about their businesses. And the best advisors are passionate about helping them succeed. When the two types get together, it&rsquo;s a beautiful thing. NYER celebrates this bond in a unique program sponsored by Citibank that recognizes the New York Tri-State area&rsquo;s top business advisors. Now in its third year, the awards attracted a record number of nominations from grateful clients who extolled their advisors&rsquo; exemplary service and the impact it has had on their business.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Spotlighting 7 top accountants, 7 top attorneys, and many happy business owners</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src="../../../app/webroot/img/gallery/Image/Jeff%20Citron%20DHCLegal.com.jpg" alt="" width="265" height="168" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Jeffrey I. Citron</strong><strong><br /> Co-Managing Partner, Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p>Last fall, Superstorm Sandy flooded the Queens-based, family-owned Madelaine Chocolate Company with five feet of ocean water during its busy pre-holiday season. Less than a year later, the company is open for business, thanks largely to the efforts of its attorney Jeffrey Citron. Citron was able to marshal his firm&rsquo;s resources to aid Madelaine, the largest employer in Queens, in numerous ways: arranging for workers to collect emergency unemployment insurance; working with a lender to restructure an $8 million line of credit; securing temporary office space for management; working with inspectors to ensure compliance for the factory&rsquo;s operations; and arranging for federal and state government officials to view the storm damage first hand, helping to pave the way for emergency relief funding. Citron, who has extensive experience in real estate and general commercial practice, also represents privately held businesses as general counsel. He specializes in assisting private and public companies in securing financing, grants, and other benefits for capital projects through government agencies and lending institutions.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nyreport.com/best_esqs_and_cpas/articles/84199/the_2013_nyer_cpa_">http://www.nyreport.com/best_esqs_and_cpas/articles/84199/the_2013_nyer_cpa_<br /></a><a href="http://www.nyreport.com/best_esqs_and_cpas/articles/84199/the_2013_nyer_cpa_esq_awards_the_advisors_you_need_to_know?page=0,1">esq_awards_the_advisors_you_need_to_know?page=0,1</a></p>', 'Best Lawyer New york city', 0x4a65666672657920436974726f6e2e20436974726f6e207761732061626c6520746f206d61727368616c20686973206669726de2809973207265736f757263657320746f20616964204d6164656c61696e652c20746865206c61726765737420656d706c6f79657220696e20517565656e732c20696e206e756d65726f75732077617973, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Nyer-Spotlights-Jeff-Citron-of-Davidoff-Hutcher-and-Citron', 0, 'Nyer Spotlights Jeff Citron of Davidoff Hutcher & Citron'),
(112, 2, 0, 'Sid Davidoff Looks Back on The Career of "Sopranos" Star James Gandolfini on "Good Day NY"', '', '2013-06-21 00:00:00', '2013-06-21 13:26:18', '<p>Sid Davidoff, along with New York Post TV Critic Linda Stassi, who were interviewed on Fox 5&rsquo;s &ldquo;Good Day New York,&rdquo; look back on the career of Sopranos star James Gandolfini.&nbsp; Sid Davidoff, Chair of the firm''s Administration Law and Governmental Relations Group, had the honor of portraying Carmela Soprano''s divorce attorney on "The Sopranos."</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.myfoxny.com/video?clipId=9010722&amp;autostart=true" target="_blank">http://www.myfoxny.com/video?clipId=9010722&amp;autostart=true</a></p>', 'James Gandolfini', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Sid-Davidoff-Looks-Back-on-The-Career-of-"Sopranos"-Star-James-Gandolfini-on-"Good-Day-NY"', 0, ''),
(118, 2, 0, 'Davidoff Hutcher & Citron Attorneys Named to 2013  "Super Lawyers" & â€œRising Starsâ€ Lists  ', '', '2013-09-17 00:00:00', '2013-09-17 08:06:42', '<h1 align="center">&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p><strong>NEW YORK, N.Y</strong>, (September 17, 2013) &ndash; Andrew Cooper, Robert Lewis, Elliot Lutzker,</p>\r\n<p>Malcolm Taub, Michael Wexelbaum and Derek Wolman, lawyers at New York-based law firm Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP, have been named to the New York Super Lawyers list as the top attorneys in New York for 2013. No more than 5 percent of the lawyers in the state are selected by Super Lawyers.&nbsp; Attorneys Joshua Krakowsky and Ron Mandel were named &ldquo;Rising Stars,&rdquo; awarded to no more than 2.5% of the lawyers in the state who are 40 or under, or who have been practicing for 10 years or less.</p>\r\n<p>Super Lawyers, a Thomson Reuters business, is a rating service of outstanding lawyers from more than 70 practice areas who have attained a high degree or peer recognition and professional achievement. The annual selections are made using a rigorous multi-phased process that includes a statewide survey of lawyers, an independent research evaluation of candidates, and peer reviews by practice area.<br /> <br /> The Super Lawyers lists are published nationwide in Super Lawyers magazines and in leading city and regional magazines across the country. Super Lawyers magazines also feature editorial profiles of attorneys who embody excellence in the practice of law. For more information about Super Lawyers, go to <a href="http://superlawyers.com">superlawyers.com</a>.<br /> <br /> The first Super Lawyers list was published in 1991 and by 2009 the rating service had expanded nationwide. In February 2010, Super Lawyers was acquired by Thomson Reuters the world''s leading source of intelligent information for business and professionals.<br /> <br /> <strong>About Davidoff &nbsp;Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP<br /> </strong>Davidoff Hutcher &amp; Citron LLP <a href="../../../">www.dhclegal.com</a>, which has over 50 attorneys in offices in New York City, Albany, Washington D.C., and Garden City, Long Island, provides legal and government relations services for a varied clientele that include Fortune 500 companies, financial institutions, prominent real estate organizations, developers, leading health and educational institutions, associations and services organizations, as well as other industries throughout the greater metropolitan area.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">For more information, please contact:</span></strong></p>\r\n<h3>Roger Ardan/ Alexandra Patchen</h3>\r\n<h3>Middleberg Communications</h3>\r\n<h3>(646) 385-8273/ (212) 812-5677</h3>\r\n<h3><a href="mailto:rardan@middlbergcommunications.com/">rardan@middlbergcommunications.com/</a></h3>\r\n<h3><a href="mailto:apatchen@middlebergcommunications.com">apatchen@middlebergcommunications.com</a></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'New York lawyers', 0x44617669646f66662048757463686572202620436974726f6e204174746f726e657973204e616d656420746f20323031332020225375706572204c61777965727322202620e2809c526973696e67205374617273e2809d2020, 0, 1, 2, 1, 'Davidoff-Hutcher-and-Citron-Attorneys-Named-to-2013--"Super-Lawyers"-and-â€œRising-Starsâ€-Lists--', 0, 'Davidoff Hutcher & Citron Attorneys Named to 2013  "Super Lawyers" & â€œRising Starsâ€  Lists'),
(114, 2, 0, 'Sid Davidoff to be honored at City College of New York 133rd Annual Alumni Dinner', '', '2013-08-13 00:00:00', '2013-08-13 12:28:48', '<p>We are pleased to announce that our founding partner, Sid Davidoff, will be honored on November 7, 2013 at the Alumni Association of the City College of New York&rsquo;s gala event&mdash;The 133<sup>rd</sup> Annual Alumni Dinner taking place at the New York Hilton.&nbsp; He will be recognized as a Townsend Harris Medalist, awarded for outstanding postgraduate achievements.</p>\r\n<p>Sid Davidoff &rsquo;60, is being recognized for his lifetime accomplishments in New York City government and outstanding legal career in government relations and land use.</p>\r\n<p>Further information about this exciting event will follow.</p>', 'City College Alumni Dinner', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Sid-Davidoff-to-be-honored-at-City-College-of-New-York-133rd-Annual-Alumni-Dinner', 0, ''),
(115, 2, 0, 'Malcolm Taub Quoted in USA Today on Celebrity Separation', '', '2013-08-28 00:00:00', '2013-08-30 08:44:58', '<p><span class="userContent">Malcolm Taub, Co-chair of our Divorce and Family Law Group, discusses the Catherine Zeta Jones/Michael Douglas Separation in USA TODAY.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class="userContent"> <a title="Click here for article" href="http://usat.ly/12Lco9s" target="_blank">http://usat.ly/12Lco9s</a></span></p>', 'Celebrity divorce', '', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Malcolm-Taub-Quoted-in-USA-Today-on-Celebrity-Separation', 0, ''),
(120, 2, 0, 'Sid Davidoff To Be Honored At City College of New Yorkâ€™s 133rd Annual Alumni Dinner November 7, 2013', '', '2013-09-17 00:00:00', '2013-09-17 20:38:25', '<p align="center">We are pleased to announce that our founding partner, Sid Davidoff, will be honored on Thursday, November 7, 2013 at the Alumni Association of the City College of New York&rsquo;s gala event&mdash;The 133<sup>rd</sup><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>Annual Alumni Dinner is taking place at the New York Hilton, 6<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;Avenue and 53<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;Street.&nbsp; A cocktail reception starts at 6:00 p.m. and dinner will be served at 7:00 p.m.&nbsp; Sid will be recognized as a Townsend Harris Medalist, awarded for outstanding postgraduate achievements.</p>\r\n<p><span>Sid Davidoff &rsquo;60, is being recognized for his lifetime accomplishments in New York City government and outstanding legal career in government relations and land use.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>If you would like to attend the dinner, tickets are $178 per person.&nbsp; Please see attached PDF registration form for additional details and to sign up.&nbsp; We ask that you also let Cecile Canna at our office know if you are attending so that we can coordinate seating arrangements.&nbsp; Cecile can be contacted at<span>&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;<a href="mailto:CXZ@dhclegal.com">CXZ@dhclegal.com</a><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>or 212-557-7200.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>To honor Sid and support City College, we also encourage you to take out an advertisement that will appear in the Gala&rsquo;s program.&nbsp; Please see separate PDF journal order form for additional details.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>We hope to see you November 7 and thank you in advance for your support.&nbsp; If you have any questions or need any additional information please contact Cecile at above contact information.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../app/webroot/img/gallery/File/133rd_Annual_alumnidinner.pdf"><span>Download the PDF here</span></a></p>\r\n<p><span><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span><br /></span></p>', 'Best New York Lawyers', 0x5369642044617669646f666620546f20426520486f6e6f726564204174204369747920436f6c6c656765206f66204e657720596f726be280997320313333726420416e6e75616c20416c756d6e692044696e6e6572204e6f76656d62657220372c2032303133, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Sid-Davidoff-To-Be-Honored-At-City-College-of-New-Yorkâ€™s-133rd-Annual-Alumni-Dinner-November-7,-2013', 0, 'Sid Davidoff To Be Honored At City College of New Yorkâ€™s 133rd Annual Alumni Dinner November 7, 2013'),
(124, 2, 0, 'WHAT HAPPENS IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT SHUTS DOWN? ', '', '2013-09-30 00:00:00', '2013-09-30 13:33:34', '<div>The failure of Congress to pass appropriations bills to fund the government for the forthcoming fiscal year, which starts October 1st, means that a Continuing Resolution (CR) must be passed by both Houses to keep the government running. In the event of a shutdown, many day-to-day services would come to a standstill as agencies send home over 800,000 non-essential employees (and incidentally order them to turn off all Government issued Blackberries and computers). National parks and museums would close. The State Department could not issue passports. SBA loan activity, which is extremely important to New York while in Hurricane Sandy recovery, would </div>', 'WHAT HAPPENS IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT SHUTS DOWN?', 0x44617669646f666620487574636865722026616d703b20436974726f6e27732064656469636174656420737461666620696e2057617368696e67746f6e2069732070726f766964696e672064657461696c656420616e616c79736973206f662074686520706f6c69746963616c2067616d6520617420706c617920746f2069747320636c69656e7473, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'WHAT-HAPPENS-IF-THE-FEDERAL-GOVERNMENT-SHUTS-DOWN?-', 0, 'WHAT HAPPENS IF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT SHUTS DOWN?');
